Priest and father of cooperative movement             Jacinta Mutura  03rd Aug 2019 02:00:00 GMT +0300 Jacinta Mutura  03rd Aug 2019 02:00:00 GMT +0300 Jacinta Mutura   Fr Joakim Gitonga at his office in Murang'a Town, on May 27,2019. Gitonga started the first registered Sacco in Kenya,1964, Mariira Parish Co-operative Savings and Credit Society. He was given dispensation from priestly obligations and allowed to marry by Pope John Paul 11, in 1975. [Kibata Kihu/Standard]    Fr Joakim Gitonga at his office in Murang'a Town, on May 27,2019. Gitonga started the first registered Sacco in Kenya,1964, Mariira Parish Co-operative Savings and Credit Society. He was given dispensation from priestly obligations and allowed to marry by Pope John Paul 11, in 1975. [Kibata Kihu/Standard] Fr Joakim Gitonga at his office in Murang'a Town, on May 27,2019. Gitonga started the first registered Sacco in Kenya,1964, Mariira Parish Co-operative Savings and Credit Society. He was given dispensation from priestly obligations and allowed to marry by Pope John Paul 11, in 1975. [Kibata Kihu/Standard] Fr Joakim Gitonga at his office in Murang'a Town, on May 27,2019. Gitonga started the first registered Sacco in Kenya,1964, Mariira Parish Co-operative Savings and Credit Society. He was given dispensation from priestly obligations and allowed to marry by Pope John Paul 11, in 1975. [Kibata Kihu/Standard]      SEE ALSO :Metropolitan National Sacco weighed down by Sh1.2b bad loans SEE ALSO : Metropolitan National Sacco weighed down by Sh1.2b bad loans      SEE ALSO :Killed by a tout? How Florence’s life was cut short SEE ALSO : Killed by a tout? How Florence’s life was cut short      SEE ALSO :Echesa moves to block auction of Sacco property SEE ALSO : Echesa moves to block auction of Sacco property      SEE ALSO :Co-op Bank supports Metropolitan National Sacco SEE ALSO : Co-op Bank supports Metropolitan National Sacco                   jmutura@standardmedia.co.ke jmutura@standardmedia.co.ke  We 